<plot>Based on Seb Hunter's honest and satirical book about his childhood, growing up in a small town with dreams of rock stardom. Hell bent for Leather charts the coming-of-age story of one boy's journey into adulthood through big hair, huge dreams and loud rock. Seb lives at home with parents that don't understand him or his music. His overbearing father, well known in local Jazz circles, constantly puts him down and rubbishes Seb's passion as merely a pipe dream. Seb sets out to prove his family wrong and sets out to become a mega rock star.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?234747</url></doc>
